00:10:15,148 --> 00:10:17,048
PLEASE...

234
00:10:17,084 --> 00:10:18,324
YOU HAVE TO FIND THE TRUTH

235
00:10:18,351 --> 00:10:20,021
ABOUT WHAT REALLY HAPPENED
TO MY DAD.

236
00:10:20,053 --> 00:10:22,693
OTHERWISE...

237
00:10:25,058 --> 00:10:27,258
...I KILLED WESLEY
FOR NOTHING.

238
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:32,970
Caroline:
GOOD MORNING.

239
00:10:34,835 --> 00:10:36,265
HEY.

240
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:37,813
DO YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

241
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,080
YOU'RE NOT NATALIE.

242
00:10:42,109 --> 00:10:44,409
I GET IT, OKAY?

243
00:10:44,444 --> 00:10:48,024
GOOD.

244
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:53,020
WHAT DID YOU SAY
YOUR NAME WAS?

245
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:56,218
CAROLINE NEWSOME.

246
00:10:56,256 --> 00:10:59,226
AND WE NEVER MET
AT A CONFERENCE OR...

247
00:10:59,259 --> 00:11:00,459
I'D HAVE REMEMBERED.

248
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:02,703
I'M VERY FAMILIAR
WITH YOUR WORK.

249
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:05,170
I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO GETTING TO KNOW YOU.

250
00:11:05,198 --> 00:11:07,968
NOW THAT YOUR MEDS
SEEM TO BE WORKING,

251
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,701
I'D LIKE TO START YOU
ON SOME INDIVIDUAL COUNSELING,

252
00:11:10,738 --> 00:11:12,038
AS WELL AS GROUP.

253
00:11:12,072 --> 00:11:14,072
[ SCOFFS ] OKAY, LET'S GET
SOMETHING STRAIGHT --

254
00:11:14,107 --> 00:11:16,377
UH, I'M NOT HERE TO GET IN TOUCH
WITH MY FEELINGS.

255
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:18,379
I'M HERE FOR THE MEDS
AND TO GET STABLE,

256
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:20,211
AND THEN I'M GETTING
THE [BLEEP] OUT,

257
00:11:20,247 --> 00:11:22,317
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHAT YOU CAN DO
RIGHT NOW.

258
00:11:22,349 --> 00:11:24,119
I'LDON'T COME BACK.R.

259
00:11:24,151 --> 00:11:27,051
YOU HEAR ME?
DON'T COME BACK!

260
00:11:27,087 --> 00:11:29,917
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK TO YOU!

261
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:33,992
MR. LEWICKI.

262
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:35,827
YOU WOULDN'T BE TRYING
TO DUCK ME, WOULD YOU?

263
00:11:35,863 --> 00:11:37,403
NO. NO, SIR.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

264
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:39,070
THEN WHY HAVEN'T YOU RETURNED
MY PHONE CALLS?

265
00:11:39,099 --> 00:11:41,369
YOU WOULDN'T BE ATTEMPTING
TO COVER UP THE REASON

266
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:44,171
PROFESSOR PIERCE HAS
CANCELED CLASSES TWO DAYS
IN A ROW, WOULD YOU?

267
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:47,809
Y-YOU SEE, UH, SIR,

268
00:11:47,841 --> 00:11:50,511
P-PROFESSOR PIERCE
HAD TO TAKE A LITTLE TRIP.

269
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:52,413
MR. LEWICKI,
I ADMIRE YOUR LOYALTY

270
00:11:52,445 --> 00:11:54,005
TO MY FRIEND DANIEL PIERCE,

271
00:11:54,047 --> 00:11:56,877
BUT I HAVE KNOWN HIM
SINCE YOU WERE WEARING HUGGIES.

272
00:11:56,917 --> 00:11:59,387
NOW TELL ME WHERE HE IS.

273
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:03,119
I'M AFRAID DR. PIERCE
IS REFUSING ALL VISITORS.

274
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:04,886
[ SIGHS ]
STUBBORN [BLEEP]

275
00:12:04,925 --> 00:12:06,455
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN
LIKE THIS.

276
00:12:06,493 --> 00:12:08,303
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
KNOWN HIM?

277
00:12:08,328 --> 00:12:10,028
WE WERE
COLLEGE ROOMMATES.

278
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:12,203
HE'S BEEN PRETTY RESISTANT
TO THERAPY.

279
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,472
WOULD YOU MIND ANSWERING
SOME QUESTIONS?

280
00:12:14,501 --> 00:12:16,341
NOT AT ALL.

281
00:12:17,437 --> 00:12:20,767
DOES HE HAVE A FRIEND
NAMED NATALIE?

282
00:12:20,808 --> 00:12:23,438
YEAH. SHE WAS DANIEL'S
GIRLFRIEND BACK IN THE DAY.

283
00:12:23,476 --> 00:12:26,276
MM.
WHAT WAS SHE LIKE?

284
00:12:26,313 --> 00:12:27,923
[ Chuckling ] YOU KNOW,
FUNNY ENOUGH, I NEVER MET HER.

285
00:12:27,948 --> 00:12:29,448
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I THOUGHT --

286
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:30,982
SEE [CHUCKLES]

287
00:12:31,018 --> 00:12:33,248
DANIEL AND I TAKE
THIS ROAD TRIP, OKAY,

288
00:12:33,286 --> 00:12:36,216
OUR JUNIOR YEAR TO
THE UNIVERSITY OF MICHIGAN.

289
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:37,456
THEIR SPRING FLING?

290
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:40,030
[ Chuckling ]
A REAL RAGER.

291
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:43,400
SUNDAY AFTERNOON, I WAKE UP
ON THE FLOOR OF SOME SORORITY,

292
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,330
AND DANIEL IS THERE.

293
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:47,095
HE'S ALL EXCITED.

294
00:12:47,134 --> 00:12:50,504
HE HAS MET THE GIRL OF
HIS DREAMS AT SOME OTHER PARTY,

295
00:12:50,537 --> 00:12:53,467
BUT, YOU KNOW,
WE HAD FINALS COMING UP,

296
00:12:53,506 --> 00:12:55,076
SO WE HAD TO GET BACK.

297
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:58,178
BUT HE STARTED A RELATIONSHIP
WITH THIS NATALIE?

298
00:12:58,211 --> 00:13:00,311
MM-HMM.
A REAL LONG-DISTANCE THING.

299
00:13:00,347 --> 00:13:02,817
HE TALKED TO HER FOR HOURS
ON THE PHONE.

300
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:04,580
HE'D VISIT HER
ON THE WEEKENDS.

301
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:08,517
BUT THEN HE, UH --
HE STARTED SHOWING SYMPTOMS.

302
00:13:10,323 --> 00:13:11,963
THEN ENDED UP
IN THE HOSPITAL.

303
00:13:11,992 --> 00:13:15,832
THANK YOU.
YOU'VE BEEN VERY HELPFUL.

304
00:13:21,902 --> 00:13:23,602
I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU
NOT TO COME BACK.

305
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,836
YOU MIGHT WANT TO HEAR
WHAT I HAVE TO SAY.

306
00:13:25,873 --> 00:13:27,243
OH, I DOUBT THAT
VERY MUCH.

307
00:13:27,274 --> 00:13:29,344
I AM NATALIE.

308
00:13:31,879 --> 00:13:33,109
WHAT THE [BLEEP] IS THIS?

309
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,076
FIRST YOU INSIST
YOU'RE NOT NATALIE,

310
00:13:35,115 --> 00:13:36,575
NOW YOU CLAIM YOU ARE?

311
00:13:36,616 --> 00:13:39,046
I-I-IF THIS IS SOME SORT OF
THERAPEUTIC TECHNIQUE,

312
00:13:39,086 --> 00:13:41,986
YOU DON'T KNOW VERY MUCH
ABOUT TREATING SCHIZOPHRENICS.

313
00:13:42,022 --> 00:13:43,922
I SPOKE TO YOUR FRIEND
PAUL HALEY.

314
00:13:43,957 --> 00:13:45,257
I DON'T WANT YOU TALKING
TO MY FRIENDS.

315
00:13:45,292 --> 00:13:47,632
HE TOLD ME ABOUT A ROAD TRIP
THE TWO OF YOU TOOK

316
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,860
TO THE UNIVERSITY
OF MSO?IGAN.

317
00:13:49,897 --> 00:13:52,397
I WENT TO MICHIGAN.

318
00:13:54,434 --> 00:13:56,244
I THINK
YOU MUST'VE SEEN ME.

319
00:14:02,175 --> 00:14:04,005
YES.

320
00:14:04,044 --> 00:14:05,884
I GOT SEPARATED FROM PAUL,

321
00:14:05,913 --> 00:14:08,223
AND I ENDED UP
AT THIS FRATERNITY

322
00:14:08,248 --> 00:14:10,248
WITH THIS BUNCH
OF IDIOTS.

323
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:13,053
THEY WERE --
THEY WERE PLAYING QUARTERS

324
00:14:13,086 --> 00:14:16,616
AND ACTING LIKE [BLEEP]
SO I WENT OUTSIDE...

325
00:14:16,656 --> 00:14:18,556
AND I SAW YOU.

326
00:14:18,591 --> 00:14:22,001
YOU WERE STANDING THERE
ALL BY YOURSELF

327
00:14:22,029 --> 00:14:25,529
AND NURSING A BEER
IN A PLASTIC CUP.

328
00:14:25,565 --> 00:14:30,565
YOU BRUSHED THIS LOOSE STRAND
OF HAIR BEHIND YOUR EAR,

329
00:14:30,603 --> 00:14:32,173
AND I THOUGHT,

330
00:14:32,205 --> 00:14:35,975
"THAT'S THE MOST BEAUTIFUL GIRL
I'VE EVER SEEN."

331
00:14:36,009 --> 00:14:38,979
AND I ALMOST WALKED AWAY,
BUT THEN...

332
00:14:39,012 --> 00:14:41,182
THIS VOICE IN MY HEAD
KEPT TELLING ME,

333
00:14:41,214 --> 00:14:42,984
"DANIEL,
DON'T BE AN IDIOT.

334
00:14:43,016 --> 00:14:44,986
"YOU'LL NEVER SEE
THIS GIRL AGAIN,

335
00:14:45,018 --> 00:14:48,118
AND YOU'LL REGRET IT FOR THE
REST OF YOUR PATHETIC LIFE."

336
00:14:48,155 --> 00:14:50,555
SO -- SO I WALKED --
[LAUGHS]

337
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:52,130
I WALKED OVER THERE,

338
00:14:52,159 --> 00:14:54,529
AND -- AND -- AND I COULD
BARELY GET MY NAME OUT,

339
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:56,531
AND YOU LAUGHED AND MADE
SOME JOKE ABOUT ENGLISH

340
00:14:56,563 --> 00:14:58,133
BEING MY SECOND LANGUAGE,

341
00:14:58,165 --> 00:15:00,925
AND -- AND WE -- WE ENDED UP
OUT ON THE GREEN,

342
00:15:00,968 --> 00:15:03,538
JUST -- JUST TALKING A-AND
LAUGHING AND HOLDING HANDS,

343
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:05,470
TALKING ABOUT RILKE
AND THE SMITHS.

344
00:15:05,505 --> 00:15:07,065
REMEMBER?

345
00:15:07,107 --> 00:15:10,037
TILL --
TILL THE SUN CAME UP.

346
00:15:10,077 --> 00:15:12,507
I WAS AT THAT PARTY.

347
00:15:14,047 --> 00:15:16,577
BUT I NEVER MET YOU.

348
00:15:16,616 --> 00:15:20,046
HOW COULD YOU FORGET?

349
00:15:20,087 --> 00:15:22,217
I DIDN'T FORGET.

350
00:15:29,529 --> 00:15:33,669
I WAS TOO SCARED
TO TALK TO YOU.

351
00:15:42,509 --> 00:15:47,449
SO THAT VOICE IN MY HEAD
WAS THE BEGINNING.

352
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:51,220
I WAS LOSING MY MIND
EARLIER THAN I THOUGHT.

353
00:15:58,558 --> 00:16:00,528
I'M SORRY.

354
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:04,360
I'D LIKE TO BE ALONE NOW.

355
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,720
OKAY. THANKS.

356
00:16:22,749 --> 00:16:25,389
HENDERSON, FROM
THE WHITE-COLLAR TASK FORCE.

357
00:16:25,418 --> 00:16:27,588
TURNS OUT THERE WAS
AN INVESTIGATION

358
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,590
OF ILLEGAL ACTIVITY
AT VERTERON.

359
00:16:29,622 --> 00:16:31,762
SO MAYBE THE KID WAS RIGHT
ABOUT HIS FATHER.

360
00:16:31,791 --> 00:16:35,501
WHY DO YOU LOOK LIKE SOMEBODY
JUST KILLED YOUR CAT?

361
00:16:35,528 --> 00:16:38,228
BECAUSE ALEX'S FATHER DIDN'T
STUMBLE ONTO SOME CONSPIRACY

362
00:16:38,265 --> 00:16:39,465
TO RIG AN ELECTION --

363
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:41,169
HE WAS THE TARGET
OF AN INVESTIGATION.

364
00:16:41,201 --> 00:16:43,371
TURNS OUT HE WAS
SELLING SOFTWARE CODE

365
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:45,213
TO VERTERON'S COMPETITORS,

366
00:16:45,238 --> 00:16:47,438
AND ON THE DAY HE DIED,
HE WAS FIRED

367
00:16:47,474 --> 00:16:50,084
AND TOLD THAT
HE WAS GONNA BE PROSECUTED.

368
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:51,380
WHICH EXPLAINS
WHY HE OFFED HIMSELF.

369
00:16:51,411 --> 00:16:53,581
DO YOU HAVE
THE ACCIDENT REPORT?

370
00:16:53,613 --> 00:16:55,123
YEAH.

371
00:16:55,148 --> 00:16:57,248
THEY FOUND A DENT
AND PAINT TRANSFER

372
00:16:57,284 --> 00:16:59,624
ON THE REAR BUMPER
OF THE REPORTER'S CAR.

373
00:16:59,652 --> 00:17:01,652
SO MAYBE SOMEBODY WAS TRYING
TO RUN HIM OFF THE ROAD.

374
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:02,758
KEEP READING.

375
00:17:02,789 --> 00:17:04,459
THE GUY'S GIRLFRIEND
TOLD THE COPS

376
00:17:04,491 --> 00:17:06,561
THAT SHE BACKED IT UP
INTO A STANCHION

377
00:17:06,593 --> 00:17:08,533
AT THE SUPERMARKET
THE WEEK BEFORE.

378
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:10,101
DID YOU CORROBORATE THAT?

379
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:13,730
KATE, WE'RE FBI AGENTS.
WE ARE NOT TRAFFIC COPS.

380
00:17:13,766 --> 00:17:15,366
[ SIGHS ]

381
00:17:15,402 --> 00:17:19,512
LOOK, I KNOW YOU CARE
ABOUT PIERCE,

382
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:22,609
BUT...I CARE ABOUT YOU,

383
00:17:22,642 --> 00:17:24,642
AND I'M STARTING TO WORRY
THAT HE'S NOT THE ONLY ONE

384
00:17:24,677 --> 00:17:27,077
THAT NEEDS
A MENTAL-HEALTH DAY.

385
00:17:27,114 --> 00:17:30,124
MAYBE I AM
A LITTLE OBSESSED.

386
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:32,690
SO, YOU KNOW,
LET'S KNOCK OFF.

387
00:17:32,719 --> 00:17:36,219
GET A COUPLE OF BEERS
AND SOME BURGERS.

388
00:17:36,256 --> 00:17:40,286
YOU GO AHEAD.
I'LL, UH, I'LL CATCH UP.

389
00:17:40,327 --> 00:17:43,097
YOU'RE GONNA CALL
THE GUY'S GIRLFRIEND

390
00:17:43,130 --> 00:17:44,630
THE SECOOH, YEAH.E, RIGHT?

391
00:17:46,599 --> 00:17:49,839
MISS CRANE,
WE'RE VERY SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

392
00:17:49,869 --> 00:17:53,839
DO YOU KNOW WHAT DAVID WAS
WORKING ON BEFORE HE DIED?

393
00:17:53,873 --> 00:17:56,583
HE WAS PARANOID
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

394
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:58,309
PARANOID IN WHAT WAY?

395
00:17:58,345 --> 00:17:59,545
HE THOUGHT PEOPLE
WERE AFTER HIM.

396
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:00,709
WHAT PEOPLE?

397
00:18:00,747 --> 00:18:02,817
I DON'T KNOW.

398
00:18:02,849 --> 00:18:05,419
MISS CRANE,
THE POLICE HAVE RULED

399
00:18:05,452 --> 00:18:08,162
YOUR BOYFRIEND'S DEATH
AN ACCIDENT,

400
00:18:08,188 --> 00:18:10,588
BUT IF YOU HAVE REASON
TO BELIEVE OTHERWISE

401
00:18:10,623 --> 00:18:11,823
AND YOU DON'T TELL US,

402
00:18:11,858 --> 00:18:13,588
YOU CAN BE CHARGED
WITH OBSTRUCTION

403
00:18:13,626 --> 00:18:15,656
AND ACCESSORY
AFTER THE FACT.

404
00:18:15,695 --> 00:18:21,395
I'M NOT SAYING
IT'S TRUE, OKAY?

405
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:25,214
BUT IF I DID SOMETHING BAD
TO HELP DAVID

406
00:18:25,238 --> 00:18:28,708
AND THAT SOMETHING BAD
GOT HIM KILLED

407
00:18:28,741 --> 00:18:33,281
[Voice breaking] CAN YOU,
YOU KNOW...PROTECT ME?

408
00:18:33,313 --> 00:18:36,223
MISS CRANE, IF YOU HAVE
KNOWLEDGE OF A CRIME

409
00:18:36,249 --> 00:18:37,719
THAT PUTS YOU IN DANGER,

410
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:40,320
WE WIL KEEP YOU SAFE.

411
00:18:46,293 --> 00:18:49,763
I WORK...
FOR THE PHONE COMPANY,

412
00:18:49,796 --> 00:18:53,226
AND DAVID WANTED THE ACCESS CODE
TO SOME GUY'S VOICEMAIL

413
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:55,466
SO HE COULD LISTEN
TO HIS MESSAGES.

414
00:18:55,502 --> 00:18:58,212
DAVID SAID
THAT THIS WAS THE STORY

415
00:18:58,238 --> 00:19:00,208
THAT COULD MAKE HIS CAREER,

416
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:01,610
SO I GAVE HIM THE CODE,

417
00:19:01,641 --> 00:19:06,351
AND WHATEVER HE HEARD
GOT HIM DRIVEN OFF THE ROAD.

418
00:19:06,379 --> 00:19:07,709
WHY DID YOU TELL THE POLICE

419
00:19:07,747 --> 00:19:09,347
THAT YOU WERE THE ONE
THAT DENTED THE CAR?

420
00:19:09,382 --> 00:19:12,292
BECAUSE WHOEVER IS OUT THERE
THAT KILLED DAVID,

421
00:19:12,319 --> 00:19:15,519
IF THEY FIND OUT WHAT I DID,
THEY MIGHT KILL ME, TOO.

422
00:19:15,555 --> 00:19:19,255
LAURA...WHOSE VOICEMAIL
DID DAVID LISTEN TO?

423
00:19:19,292 --> 00:19:23,632
A MAN NAMED LEO ATTINGER.

424
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:29,195
LEO ATTINGER IS THE NEW
SENATOR'S CHIEF OF STAFF.

425
00:19:29,236 --> 00:19:31,766
Leo:
SO, WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

426
00:19:31,804 --> 00:19:34,514
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH A STAR-HERALD REPORTER

427
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:35,681
NAMED DAVID ALCOTT --

428
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,678
HE DIED RECENTLY
IN A CAR ACCIDENT?

429
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:39,650
YEAH, I HEARD ABOUT THAT.

430
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:40,979
WE'RE INVESTIGATING
ALLEGATIONS

431
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,583
THAT HE WAS
HACKING CELLPHONES,

432
00:19:42,615 --> 00:19:44,545
AND WE BELIEVE THAT
YOU MAY HAVE BEEN A VICTIM.

433
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:48,956
SO THAT EXPLAINS IT.

434
00:19:48,988 --> 00:19:51,688
EXPLAINS WHAT?

435
00:19:51,724 --> 00:19:52,794
AFTER THE PLANE CRASH,

436
00:19:52,825 --> 00:19:54,355
THERE WAS SPECULATION

437
00:19:54,394 --> 00:19:56,264
THAT THE GOVERNOR
WOULD APPOINT HELEN PAULSON,

438
00:19:56,296 --> 00:19:58,396
THE SENATOR'S WIDOW,
TO SERVE OUT HIS TERM,

439
00:19:58,431 --> 00:19:59,971
BUT SHE CALLED
A PRESS CONFERENCE

440
00:19:59,999 --> 00:20:02,699
AND ANNOUNCED THAT SHE WOULDN'T
ACCEPT THE APPOINTMENT.

441
00:20:02,735 --> 00:20:03,895
AND ENDORSED RYLAND,
RIGHT?

442
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:05,866
WELL, THE NIGHT BEFORE

443
00:20:05,905 --> 00:20:07,765
MRS. PAULSON MADE
THAT ANNOUNCEMENT,

444
00:20:07,807 --> 00:20:10,677
SHE LEFT ME A VERY STRANGE
VOICEMAIL MESSAGE.

445
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,450
SAYING WHAT?

446
00:20:12,479 --> 00:20:14,949
SHE SAID SHE'D GOTTEN
THE FILTHY PACKAGE I'D SENT

447
00:20:14,981 --> 00:20:17,851
AND SHE WAS GONNA WITHDRAW
HER NAME FROM CONSIDERATION.

448
00:20:17,884 --> 00:20:19,924
DID YOU SEND HER A PACKAGE?

449
00:20:19,952 --> 00:20:22,462
I HAD NO IDEA WHAT SHE WAS
TALKING ABOUT,

450
00:20:22,489 --> 00:20:26,259
BUT HER HUSBAND
WAS RYLAND'S MENTOR,

451
00:20:26,293 --> 00:20:28,663
SO I ASKED RYLAND AND THE REST
OF THE CAMPAIGN STAFF

452
00:20:28,695 --> 00:20:31,855
IF ANYBODY KNEW ANYTHING
ABOUT IT, AND NOBODY DID.

453
00:20:31,898 --> 00:20:33,998
AND YOU THINK DAVID ALCOTT
HEARD THIS VOICEMAIL MESSAGE?

454
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:35,873
HE CAME TO ME,

455
00:20:35,902 --> 00:20:37,472
INSINUATING THAT
I HAD BLACKMAILED MRS. PAULSON

456
00:20:37,504 --> 00:20:38,814
INTO DROPPING OUT

457
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:40,908
SO THAT I COULD GET
SENATOR RYLAND ELECTED.

458
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:43,910
I DIDN'T KNOW WHERE THE [BLEEP]
HE WAS GETTING THAT FROM.

459
00:20:43,943 --> 00:20:45,283
NOW I DO.

460
00:20:45,312 --> 00:20:46,852
YEAH, WELL,
YOU GOT TO ADMIT,

461
00:20:46,879 --> 00:20:48,449
THINGS TURNED OUT PRETTY WELL
FOR YOU AND YOUR CANDIDATE.

462
00:20:48,481 --> 00:20:50,721
WELL...

463
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,690
I'M NOT GONNA LIE TO YOU,
AGENT MORETTI.

464
00:20:52,719 --> 00:20:56,559
IN THE WORLD OF
BARE-KNUCKLED ILLINOIS POLITICS,

465
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:59,889
STRONG-ARMING A WIDOW OUT
OF ACCEPTING HER HUSBAND'S SEAT

466
00:20:59,926 --> 00:21:01,856
SO THAT I CAN GET
MY GUY THE JOB?

467
00:21:01,894 --> 00:21:03,364
THAT'D BE QUITE A COUP.

468
00:21:03,396 --> 00:21:06,866
BUT...I HAD NOTHING TO DO
WITH IT.

469
00:21:06,899 --> 00:21:08,299
WANT A JELLYBEAN?

470
00:21:10,002 --> 00:21:13,312
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

471
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:17,640
JUST PEACHY, THANKS.

472
00:21:17,677 --> 00:21:19,877
I HAVE TO ADMIT,
I'M CURIOUS.

473
00:21:19,912 --> 00:21:22,382
I WOULD'VE THOUGHT, AFTER
YOU GOT OUT OF THE HOSPITAL,

474
00:21:22,415 --> 00:21:24,045
YOU WOULD'VE GONE LOOKING
FOR NATALIE

475
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:25,653
AND FOUND OUT
SHE WASN'T REAL.

476
00:21:25,685 --> 00:21:27,615
I KNEW MY PROGNOSIS.

477
00:21:27,654 --> 00:21:30,494
NO CURE,
INEVITABLE RELAPSES,

478
00:21:30,523 --> 00:21:35,093
TERRIBLE SIDE EFFECTS FROM
PRIMITIVE SOUL-SUCKING MEDS.

479
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,827
THE NATALIE I KNEW WOULD'VE
TRIED TO TAKE CARE OF ME.

480
00:21:38,865 --> 00:21:41,595
I COULDN'T STAND
THE THOUGHT OF THAT,

481
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:45,344
SO I DECIDED IT WAS BETTER
TO HAVE NO CONTACT AT ALL.

482
00:21:45,372 --> 00:21:47,512
BUT YOU DID SEE HER AGAIN.

483
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:51,080
I'M A CLASSIC CASE.

484
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:53,480
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

485
00:21:53,513 --> 00:21:56,883
I GOT MY DEGREES.
I WAS TEACHING AND WRITING.

486
00:21:56,916 --> 00:22:00,086
I THOUGHT, "HEY,
I'VE BEATEN THIS THING."

487
00:22:00,119 --> 00:22:02,619
SO YOU WEANED YOURSELF
OFF THE MEDS.

488
00:22:02,655 --> 00:22:06,755
THEN ONE DAY,
THERE'S A KNOCK ON THE DOOR,

489
00:22:06,793 --> 00:22:09,063
AND IT'S NATALIE.

490
00:22:09,095 --> 00:22:11,395
AND SHE SAID, "HEY, YOU.

491
00:22:11,431 --> 00:22:15,441
GUESS WHO JUST GOT
A TEACHING JOB AT CLMU."

492
00:22:15,468 --> 00:22:17,568
[ SCOFFS ]

493
00:22:17,604 --> 00:22:20,844
AND I WAS OVER THE MOON.

494
00:22:20,873 --> 00:22:22,143
BUT AT SOME POINT,

495
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,044
YOU REALIZED THAT
SHE WASN'T REALLY THERE.

496
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:26,106
WE WERE
AT THE FIELD MUSEUM,

497
00:22:26,145 --> 00:22:29,415
AND I WAS LAUGHING MY [BLEEP]
OFF AT SOMETHING FUNNY

498
00:22:29,449 --> 00:22:31,849
SHE SAID ABOUT
THE PACHYDERM DIORAMA,

499
00:22:31,884 --> 00:22:33,494
AND THIS
LITTLE KID TAPS ME.

500
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:35,490
HE SAYS, "HEY, MISTER.

501
00:22:35,522 --> 00:22:37,792
WHY ARE YOU TALKING
TO YOURSELF?"

502
00:22:39,626 --> 00:22:41,026
AND I LOOKED AROUND,

503
00:22:41,060 --> 00:22:43,700
AND I...REALIZED THAT EVERYBODY
WAS STARING AT ME

504
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:45,130
INSTEAD OF THE ELEPHANTS.

505
00:22:45,164 --> 00:22:46,874
THAT MUST'VE BEEN PAINFUL.

506
00:22:48,535 --> 00:22:51,465
I LIKED
HAVING HER AROUND.

507
00:22:51,504 --> 00:22:55,814
EVEN IF IT MEANT GETTING
STARED AT ONCE IN A WHILE.

508
00:22:55,842 --> 00:22:59,612
WHEN THINGS GOT REALLY BAD,
I TRIED THE LATEST DRUG,

509
00:22:59,646 --> 00:23:03,016
AND NATALIE AND THE OTHER
LESS-PLEASANT VISITORS

510
00:23:03,049 --> 00:23:04,549
WOULD GO AWAY.

511
00:23:04,584 --> 00:23:07,754
OR AT LEAST THEY WOULDN'T
COME AROUND AS OFTEN.

512
00:23:07,787 --> 00:23:10,157
AND I'D THINK,
"OKAY, THIS TIME --

513
00:23:10,189 --> 00:23:12,629
THIS TIME
I'VE GOT IT LICKED."

514
00:23:12,659 --> 00:23:15,429
AND THEN THE CYCLE
WOULD START AGAIN.

515
00:23:15,462 --> 00:23:19,432
BUT I ALWAYS BELIEVED

516
00:23:19,466 --> 00:23:24,036
THERE WAS THIS ONE
BEAUTIFUL SUMMER,

517
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:27,970
BEFORE I BECAME
A COMPLETE WACKO,

518
00:23:28,007 --> 00:23:32,207
WHERE I HAD
WHAT NORMAL PEOPLE HAVE --

519
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,814
SOMEONE TO LOVE.

520
00:23:34,847 --> 00:23:36,777
SOMETHING REAL.

521
00:23:38,585 --> 00:23:41,085
AND NOW I LOOK AT YOU,

522
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:44,890
THE MOST FAMILIAR STRANGER
I'VE EVER MET...

523
00:23:47,494 --> 00:23:51,734
...AND I KNOW
I NEVER HAD IT AT ALL.

524
00:23:53,165 --> 00:23:57,095
I'M SORRY...

525
00:23:57,136 --> 00:24:01,466
THAT I'M NOT THE PERSON
YOU THOUGHT I WAS.

526
00:24:01,508 --> 00:24:03,708
TRULY.

527
00:24:06,178 --> 00:24:07,478
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

528
00:24:07,514 --> 00:24:08,924
TELL ME, DOCTOR,

529
00:24:08,948 --> 00:24:11,678
IN YOUR
PROFESSIONAL OPINION,

530
00:24:11,718 --> 00:24:13,118
WHAT'S MORE SERIOUS --

531
00:24:13,152 --> 00:24:16,022
HALLUCINATING A LIFELONG
FRIENDSHIP THAT NEVER EXISTED

532
00:24:16,055 --> 00:24:19,155
OR WITNESSING A BRUTAL BUT
COMPLETELY IMAGINARY MURDER?

533
00:24:20,693 --> 00:24:24,563
YOUR FRIEND FROM THE FBI CAME BY
A COUPLE OF DAYS AGO.

534
00:24:24,597 --> 00:24:27,167
IT TURNS OUT THAT THE CRIME
YOU WITNESSED

535
00:24:27,199 --> 00:24:29,099
ACTUALLY DID HAPPEN.

536
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:34,973
YOU KNEW THIS,
AND YOU DIDN'T TELL ME?

537
00:24:35,007 --> 00:24:36,177
I DIDN'T WANT
TO SET YOU BACK.

538
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:38,708
WELL, YOU BLEW THAT GOAL.

539
00:24:38,745 --> 00:24:40,545
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
DR. PIERCE?

540
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:42,110
I'M GETTING THE [BLEEP]
OUT OF HERE.

541
00:24:42,148 --> 00:24:43,818
IF YOU LEAVE,
THE CYCLE WILL START AGAIN.

542
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:45,120
YOU'LL BE BACK,

543
00:24:45,151 --> 00:24:46,791
MAYBE IN A COUPLE OF DAYS,
MAYBE IN SIX MONTHS.

544
00:24:46,819 --> 00:24:49,619
ARE YOU THREATENING TO HAVE ME
LEGALLY COMMITTED?

545
00:24:49,656 --> 00:24:52,116
BECAUSE OTHERWISE,
I'M CALLING A CAB.

546
00:24:52,158 --> 00:24:53,828
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

547
00:24:55,962 --> 00:24:57,802
DANIEL,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

548
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:59,730
I-I WANT BACK IN
ON THIS CASE.

549
00:24:59,766 --> 00:25:01,996
SHOULDN'T YOU BE
IN THE HOSPITAL?

550
00:25:02,034 --> 00:25:03,274
NO, I'M DOING BETTER.

551
00:25:03,302 --> 00:25:04,742
THE MEDS ARE WORKING,
BUT I KNOW MYSELF.

552
00:25:04,771 --> 00:25:06,241
THE BEST TREATMENT
FOR ME RIGHT NOW

553
00:25:06,272 --> 00:25:07,872
IS TO HELP YOU
SOLVE THIS THING.

554
00:25:07,907 --> 00:25:09,937
I DON'T KNOW
IF PLEASE, KATE. --

555
00:25:09,976 --> 00:25:13,676
I NEED YOU
TO LET ME DO THIS.

556
00:25:16,182 --> 00:25:17,322
OKAY.

557
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:19,089
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

558
00:25:19,118 --> 00:25:21,518
COME ON IN.
I'LL MAKE YOU A CUP OF TEA.

559
00:25:31,197 --> 00:25:32,927
Kate: MRS. PAULSON,

560
00:25:32,965 --> 00:25:36,195
LEO ATTINGER SAYS THAT YOU
LEFT HIM AN ANGRY VOICEMAIL

561
00:25:36,235 --> 00:25:39,605
IMPLYING THAT HE'D SENT YOU
SOME SORT OF A PACKAGE

562
00:25:39,639 --> 00:25:43,039
THAT CAUSED YOU TO TURN DOWN
YOUR HUSBAND'S SENATE SEAT?

563
00:25:43,075 --> 00:25:46,905
LEO ATTINGER IS
A REPREHENSIBLE HUMAN BEING

564
00:25:46,946 --> 00:25:51,716
WHO WOULD STEP ON HIS OWN MOTHER
TO ADVANCE HIS CAREER.

565
00:25:51,751 --> 00:25:53,951
I ASSUME THAT WHATEVER
WAS IN THIS PACKAGE

566
00:25:53,986 --> 00:25:55,886
WAS INCRIMINATING
OR EMBARRASSING.

567
00:25:55,922 --> 00:25:58,322
OTHERWISE, YOU WOULD'VE
ALERTED THE AUTHORITIES?

568
00:25:58,357 --> 00:26:00,057
I'M SORRY, AGENT MORETTI.

569
00:26:00,092 --> 00:26:02,602
I CAN'T CONTINUE
THIS CONVERSATION.

570
00:26:02,629 --> 00:26:03,799
MA'AM, IT'S POSSIBLE
THAT DAVID ALCOTT,

571
00:26:03,830 --> 00:26:05,160
A REPORTER
FOR THE STAR-HERALD,

572
00:26:05,197 --> 00:26:07,927
WAS MURDERED FOR PURSUING
A STORY ABOUT THIS.

573
00:26:07,967 --> 00:26:10,267
NOW, PLEASE TELL ME
WHAT YOU KNOW.

574
00:26:12,705 --> 00:26:14,335
[ SIGHS ]

575
00:26:14,373 --> 00:26:17,243
I GOT AN ENVELOPE
IN THE MAIL.

576
00:26:17,276 --> 00:26:20,806
IT HAD A FLASH-DRIVE THING
AND A NOTE.

577
00:26:20,847 --> 00:26:23,947
"IT WOULD BE BETTER
FOR THE PEOPLE OF ILLINOIS

578
00:26:23,983 --> 00:26:25,353
"AND YOUR LATE HUSBAND

579
00:26:25,384 --> 00:26:28,094
"IF YOU TURNED DOWN
THE APPOINTMENT...

580
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:30,890
AND YOU ENDORSED
SCOTT RYLAND."

581
00:26:31,858 --> 00:26:34,688
WHAT WAS
ON THE FLASH DRIVE?

582
00:26:36,228 --> 00:26:38,668
A VIDEO.

583
00:26:38,698 --> 00:26:42,368
OF TED IN HIS OFFICE...

584
00:26:42,401 --> 00:26:43,871
WITH A WOMAN.

585
00:26:46,305 --> 00:26:48,035
DO YOU KNOW
WHO THE WOMAN WAS?

586
00:26:48,074 --> 00:26:51,744
VICTORIA RYLAND.

587
00:26:52,879 --> 00:26:54,609
THE WIFE
OF THE NEW SENATOR?

588
00:26:56,783 --> 00:26:58,723
Victoria:
LET GO OF ME!

589
00:26:58,751 --> 00:27:00,151
LET GO OF ME!.

590
00:27:00,186 --> 00:27:01,246
ALL RIGHT.
I THOUGHT YOU WANTED TO.

591
00:27:01,287 --> 00:27:03,087
YOU THOUGHT WRONG.

592
00:27:03,122 --> 00:27:04,892
OKAY. OKAY.

593
00:27:04,924 --> 00:27:07,334
ALL RIGHT, BUT NOBODY ELSE
HAS TO KNOW ABOUT THIS, RIGHT?

594
00:27:07,359 --> 00:27:09,759
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?

595
00:27:09,796 --> 00:27:11,696
Kate:
HELEN PAULSON.

596
00:27:11,731 --> 00:27:13,931
SOMEBODY SENT IT TO HER
TO BLACKMAIL HER

597
00:27:13,966 --> 00:27:16,266
INTO TURNING DOWN
HER HUSBAND'S SENATE SEAT

598
00:27:16,302 --> 00:27:18,872
SO THAT YOUR HUSBAND
COULD RUN IN HIS PLACE.

599
00:27:18,905 --> 00:27:21,835
ARE YOU IMPLYING THAT I HAD
SOMETHING TO DO WITH THAT?

600
00:27:21,874 --> 00:27:24,414
THE MAN TRIED TO RAPE ME.

601
00:27:24,443 --> 00:27:26,713
BUT YOU NEVER REPORTED IT.

602
00:27:26,746 --> 00:27:28,276
[ SCOFFS ]

603
00:27:28,314 --> 00:27:29,784
HE WAS A SENATOR...

604
00:27:29,816 --> 00:27:31,746
AND MY HUSBAND'S HERO.

605
00:27:31,784 --> 00:27:34,294
AND THEN HE DIED
IN A PLANE CRASH.

606
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,420
WHAT WOULD'VE BEEN THE POINT
OF RUINING HIS REPUTATION?

607
00:27:36,455 --> 00:27:38,215
WHAT WERE YOU DOING IN HIS
OFFICE THAT LATE AT NIGHT?

608
00:27:38,257 --> 00:27:41,427
I HAD BEEN TRYING TO GET
A MEETING WITH HIM FOR WEEKS

609
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:44,130
TO DISCUSS FUNDING
FOR A LITERACY PROGRAM.

610
00:27:44,163 --> 00:27:46,903
WHEN I FINALLY GOT IN
TO SEE HIM,

611
00:27:46,933 --> 00:27:50,273
I-I STARTED TO TALK TO HIM
ABOUT THE PROGRAM.

612
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:55,782
HE CAME OVER, SAT NEXT TO ME
ON THE COUCH, AND JUST...

613
00:27:55,808 --> 00:27:57,378
POUNCED ON ME.

614
00:27:57,409 --> 00:28:00,849
I-I GOT OUT
AS FAST AS I COULD.

615
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:02,780
DID ANYBODY
SEE YOU LEAVE?

616
00:28:02,815 --> 00:28:04,445
UH...

617
00:28:04,483 --> 00:28:06,823
LEO ATTINGER.

618
00:28:09,288 --> 00:28:12,058
YOUR HUSBAND'S
CHIEF OF STAFF?

619
00:28:12,091 --> 00:28:14,191
W-WHAT WAS HE DOING THERE?

620
00:28:14,226 --> 00:28:18,056
UM, BEFORE LEO WORKED
FOR SCOTT,

621
00:28:18,097 --> 00:28:19,427
HE WAS AN AIDE
TO SENATOR PAULSON.

622
00:28:19,465 --> 00:28:22,895
WHEN DID YOUR HUSBAND
HIRE HIM?

623
00:28:22,935 --> 00:28:24,795
RIGHT AFTER
SENATOR PAULSON DIED.

624
00:28:24,837 --> 00:28:26,767
EVERYONE THOUGHT
THAT THE GOVERNOR

625
00:28:26,806 --> 00:28:28,506
WAS GOING TO APPOINT
MRS. PAULSON,

626
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:29,880
BUT LEO CAME TO SCOTT,

627
00:28:29,909 --> 00:28:31,479
SAID HE COULD
GET HIM ELECTED.

628
00:28:33,512 --> 00:28:35,712
UH-HUH.

629
00:28:39,318 --> 00:28:42,488
MR. ATTINGER!

630
00:28:42,521 --> 00:28:44,191
WE WERE JUST HOPING TO ASK YOU
A FEW MORE QUESTIONS,

631
00:28:44,223 --> 00:28:45,223
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

632
00:28:45,257 --> 00:28:47,227
I'M A LITTLE BUSY.

633
00:28:47,259 --> 00:28:49,199
WE WANT TO KNOW WHETHER OR NOT
YOU HAD ACCESS

634
00:28:49,228 --> 00:28:50,398
TO ANY OF THE SECURITY TAPES

635
00:28:50,429 --> 00:28:51,899
RECORDED AT
SENATOR PAULSON'S OFFICE

636
00:28:51,931 --> 00:28:53,431
FROM WHEN YOU WORKED THERE.

637
00:28:53,465 --> 00:28:54,795
[ Chuckling ] I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

638
00:28:54,834 --> 00:28:56,804
Man: LEO?

639
00:28:56,836 --> 00:28:58,366
HI, THANKS SO MUCH
FOR COMING.

640
00:28:58,404 --> 00:29:00,974
SENATOR, TELL ME.

641
00:29:01,007 --> 00:29:02,837
WERE YOU COMPLICIT IN STEALING
YOUR CONGRESSIONAL SEAT,

642
00:29:02,875 --> 00:29:04,475
OR ARE YOU JUST A PUPPET
FOR THE REAL POWER BROKERS?

643
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:06,110
I-I BEG YOUR PARDON?

644
00:29:06,145 --> 00:29:07,205
WE'RE GONNA TAKE A WALK.

645
00:29:07,246 --> 00:29:09,776
[ SCOFFS ]

646
00:29:09,816 --> 00:29:10,846
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT,
SENATOR.

647
00:29:10,883 --> 00:29:12,153
LISTEN, UM...

648
00:29:12,184 --> 00:29:13,394
SEND SOMEBODY OUT
TO GET ME A BURGER.

649
00:29:13,419 --> 00:29:15,019
YOU KNOW,
THEY'RE SERVING SALMON.

650
00:29:15,054 --> 00:29:16,564
YOU KNOW
I CAN'T EAT SALMON.

651
00:29:16,588 --> 00:29:18,858
STAY ON SUPPOSED TO HAVE
TOPPEDDANIEL?THINGS.

652
00:29:18,891 --> 00:29:22,091
SENATOR,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

653
00:29:22,128 --> 00:29:23,958
[ MUTTERING ]

654
00:29:23,996 --> 00:29:25,496
NO, HE'S NOT ALL RIGHT.
HE'S HAVING A STROKE.

655
00:29:25,531 --> 00:29:27,231
WHAT? NO. SENATOR!

656
00:29:28,367 --> 00:29:31,397
CALL AN AMBULANCE.

657
00:29:38,144 --> 00:29:40,554
Daniel:
RYLAND DIDN'T MAKE IT.

658
00:29:40,579 --> 00:29:42,279
LET'S GIVE THE FAMILY
SOME PRIVACY.

659
00:29:42,314 --> 00:29:43,354
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

660
00:29:43,382 --> 00:29:46,022
CAN I HELP YOU?

661
00:29:46,052 --> 00:29:47,852
I'M DR. DANIEL PIERCE.

662
00:29:47,887 --> 00:29:49,557
I WAS THE ONE WHO FIRST NOTICED
THE SENATOR STROKING OUT.

663
00:29:49,588 --> 00:29:51,558
YOU WERE
HIS PERSMM-HMM.YSICIAN?

664
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:54,030
DID HE HAVE ANY HISTORY
OF STROKENO. CLOTTING?

665
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:56,400
NOW,
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME.

666
00:29:56,428 --> 00:29:57,898
ORDER AN AUTOPSY.

667
00:29:57,930 --> 00:29:59,100
TELL THEM TO TEST
FOR CLOTTING AGENTS

668
00:29:59,131 --> 00:30:00,401
THAT COULD'VE CAUSED
A STROKE.

669
00:30:00,432 --> 00:30:02,032
WHY?
YOU DON'T THINK SOMEBODY --

670
00:30:02,068 --> 00:30:03,268
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M THINKING.

671
00:30:03,302 --> 00:30:04,342
THERE ARE TOO MANY
BODIES DROPPING

672
00:30:04,370 --> 00:30:05,400
FOR THIS
TO BE A COINCIDENCE.

673
00:30:05,437 --> 00:30:06,907
DANIEL,
THERE'S NO EVIDENCE.

674
00:30:06,939 --> 00:30:08,239
THAT'S WHY WE NEED
A TOX SCREEN, KATE.

675
00:30:08,274 --> 00:30:10,014
I'M TELLING YOU,
SOMEBODY KILLED HIM!

676
00:30:10,042 --> 00:30:12,012
WHAT!?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?!

677
00:30:12,044 --> 00:30:13,414
JUST PLEASE STAY CALM.

678
00:30:13,445 --> 00:30:16,045
Get your crackpot friend
out of here, Agent Moretti.

679
00:30:16,082 --> 00:30:18,022
OF COURSE YOU WANT ME
OUT OF HERE, ATTINGER.

680
00:30:18,050 --> 00:30:19,490
OF COURSE YOU DO!

681
00:30:19,518 --> 00:30:21,248
YOU CAN'T HIDE
THE TRUTH FOREVER!

682
00:30:23,055 --> 00:30:25,185
I'M ONTO YOU, ATTINGER!

683
00:30:29,628 --> 00:30:32,258
DOC, LET ME MAKE YOU
A CUP OF TEA.

684
00:30:32,298 --> 00:30:34,168
I DON'T WANT TEA, LEWICKI.
I WANT ANSWERS!

685
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,200
[ BEEP ]

686
00:30:35,234 --> 00:30:37,174
WELL,
I GOT SOME FOR YOU.

